# AMR-GigaWord 200k

# ::id 0 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok the european union 's foreign policy chief , javier solana , said tuesday that the deteriorating government and security situation in the gaza strip should serve as impetus for the palestinian authority to give more power to the prime minister .
# ::alignments
(s / say-01
      :ARG0 (p / person
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "Javier"
                  :op2 "Solana")
            :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                  :ARG1 (o / organization
                        :name (n2 / name
                              :op1 "European"
                              :op2 "Union"))
                  :ARG2 (c / chief
                        :topic (p2 / policy-01
                              :ARG2 (f / foreign)))))
      :ARG1 (r / recommend-01
            :ARG1 (s2 / serve-01
                  :ARG0 (d / deteriorate-01
                        :ARG1 (a / and
                              :op1 (s3 / situation
                                    :mod (g / government-organization
                                          :ARG0-of (g2 / govern-01)))
                              :op2 (s4 / situation
                                    :mod (s5 / security))
                              :location (s6 / strip
                                    :mod (g3 / gaza))))
                  :ARG1 (ii / impetus)
                  :ARG2 (a2 / authority
                        :mod (c2 / country
                              :name (n3 / name
                                    :op1 "Palestine")))
                  :purpose (g4 / give-01
                        :ARG0 a2
                        :ARG1 (p3 / power
                              :mod (m / more))
                        :ARG2 (p4 / person
                              :ARG0-of (h2 / have-org-role-91
                                    :ARG2 (m2 / minister
                                          :mod (p5 / prime)))))))
      :time (d2 / date-entity
            :weekday (t / tuesday)))

# ::id 1 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok the number of shanghai airlines weekly flights from shanghai to macao has increased from two to four , as more people are traveling between the two cities prior to the upcoming return of macao to china .
# ::alignments
(c / cause-01
      :ARG0 (t / travel-01
            :ARG0 (p / person
                  :ARG1-of (h / have-quant-91
                        :ARG3 (m / more)))
            :ARG1 (b / between
                  :op1 (c2 / city
                        :name (n / name
                              :op1 "Shanghai"))
                  :op2 (c3 / city
                        :name (n2 / name
                              :op1 "Macao")))
            :time (p2 / prior
                  :op1 (r / return-01
                        :ARG1 c2
                        :ARG4 (c4 / country
                              :name (n3 / name
                                    :op1 "China"))
                        :time (u / upcoming))))
      :ARG1 (ii / increase-01
            :ARG1 (n4 / number
                  :quant-of (a / airline
                        :source c2
                        :frequency (r2 / rate-entity-91
                              :ARG3 (t2 / temporal-quantity
                                    :quant 1
                                    :unit (w / week)))))
            :ARG4 a
            :source c2))

# ::id 2 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok a man who took over a westchester company 's internet service to send millions of anonymous e-mails about pornography and get-rich-quick schemes has pleaded guilty to forgery .
# ::alignments
(p / plead-02
      :ARG0 (m / man
            :ARG0-of (t / take-over-12
                  :ARG1 (s / service
                        :mod (ii / internet)
                        :poss (c / company
                              :location (w / westchester)))
                  :purpose (s2 / send-01
                        :ARG0 m
                        :ARG1 (e / email-01
                              :quant (m2 / multiple
                                    :op1 1000000)
                              :mod (a / anonymous)
                              :topic (a2 / and
                                    :op1 (p2 / pornography)
                                    :op2 (s3 / scheme-01
                                          :ARG1 (g / get-01
                                                :ARG1 (r / rich))
                                          :ARG1-of (q / quick-02)))))))
      :ARG1 (g2 / guilty-01
            :ARG1 m
            :ARG2 (f / forgery))
      :ARG2 m)

# ::id 3 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

            :mod (s / state))

            :ARG0 (g / government-organization
                  :name (n / name
                        :op1 "Interior"
                        :op2 "Ministry")
                  :mod (c / country
                        :name (n2 / name
                              :op1 "Iran")))
            :ARG1 (e / extend-01
                  :ARG0 g
                  :ARG1 (t2 / time
                        :time-of (p / poll-01))
                  :ARG2 (m / multiple
                        :op1 (t3 / temporal-quantity
                              :quant 1
                              :unit (m2 / minute)))
                  :ARG4 (r2 / runoff-02
                        :ARG1 (e2 / elect-01
                              :ARG2 (p2 / president))
                        :ord (o / ordinal-entity
                              :value 1)
                        :time (s2 / since
                              :op1 (r3 / revolution-03
                                    :ARG1 (r4 / religious-group
                                          :name (n3 / name
                                                :op1 "Islam")))))))
      :time (d2 / date-entity
            :weekday (f / friday)
            :dayperiod (n4 / night)))

# ::id 4 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok the european union handed the management of its vast new global diplomatic corps to a frenchman on monday as foreign affairs chief catherine ashton named france 's us ambassador her deputy .

            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "European"
                  :op2 "Union"))
      :ARG1 (m / manage-01
            :ARG0 o
            :ARG1 (c / corps
                  :mod (d / diplomacy)
                  :mod (g / globe)
                  :ARG1-of (n2 / new-01)
                  :mod (v / vast)
                  :poss o))
      :ARG2 (p / person
            :mod (c2 / country
                  :name (n3 / name
                        :op1 "France"))
            :ARG0-of (h2 / have-org-role-91
                  :ARG2 (c3 / chief
                        :topic (a / affair-02
                              :ARG2 (f / foreign))))
            :ARG1-of (n4 / name-01
                  :ARG2 (p2 / person
                        :name (n5 / name
                              :op1 "Catherine"
                              :op2 "Ashton")
                        :ARG0-of (h3 / have-org-role-91
                              :ARG1 c2
                              :ARG2 (a2 / ambassador
                                    :mod (c4 / country
                                          :name (n6 / name
                                                :op1 "United"
                                                :op2 "States"))))
                        :ARG0-of (h4 / have-org-role-91
                              :ARG2 (d2 / deputy)))))
      :time (d3 / date-entity
            :weekday (m2 / monday)))

# ::id 5 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok lending rates on three-month dollar loans between banks rose for the third day running tuesday amid ongoing concerns about the state of the u.s. banking system after the bailout of citigroup inc. , but the equivalent rates for euros and pounds continued to fall .
# ::alignments
(c / contrast-01
      :ARG1 (r / rise-01
            :ARG1 (r2 / rate
                  :mod (l / loan-01
                        :ARG0 (b / bank)
                        :ARG1 (m / monetary-quantity
                              :quant 3
                              :unit (d / dollar))
                        :ARG2 (b2 / bank)
                        :duration (t / temporal-quantity
                              :quant 3
                              :unit (m2 / month))))
            :time (d2 / date-entity
                  :weekday (t2 / tuesday))
            :ARG1-of (c2 / cause-01
                  :ARG0 (c3 / concern-01
                        :ARG0 (s / state
                              :poss (s2 / system
                                    :mod (b3 / bank)
                                    :mod (c4 / country
                                          :name (n / name
                                                :op1 "U.S.")))
                              :time (a / after
                                    :op1 (b4 / bail-out-02
                                          :ARG1 (c5 / company
                                                :name (n2 / name
                                                      :op1 " citigroup"
                                                      :op2 "Inc.")))))
                        :ARG1-of (g / go-on-15))))
      :ARG2 (c6 / continue-01
            :ARG1 (f / fall-01
                  :ARG1 (r3 / rate
                        :mod (e / equivalent)
                        :mod m
                        :quant 1
                        :unit (e2 / euro))
                  :mod (p / pound))))

# ::id 6 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok sony corp. of america signed a sponsorship agreement with the national basketball association worth more than $ ## million , giving the company the rights to develop <unk> movies and television shows .
# ::alignments
(s / sign-02
      :ARG0 (c / company
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "S.C."
                  :op2 "of"
                  :op3 "Americaa"))
      :ARG1 (a / agree-01
            :ARG1 (s2 / sponsor-01)
            :ARG2 (a2 / association
                  :mod (b / basketball)
                  :mod (n2 / nation))
            :ARG1-of (w / worth-01
                  :ARG2 (m / more-than
                        :op1 (m2 / monetary-quantity
                              :quant 1000000000
                              :unit (d / dollar)))))
      :ARG0-of (g / give-01
            :ARG1 (r / right-05
                  :ARG1 c
                  :ARG2 (d2 / develop-02
                        :ARG0 c
                        :ARG1 (a3 / and
                              :op1 (m3 / movie)
                              :op2 (s3 / show-04
                                    :ARG3 (t / television)))))
            :ARG2 c))

# ::id 7 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

            :op2 (f2 / fast-02))
      :time (b / begin-01
            :ARG1 (ii / inquest
                  :topic (t2 / thing
                        :ARG1-of (d / describe-01
                              :ARG0 (n / newspaper)
                              :ARG2 (g / game
                                    :name (n2 / name
                                          :op1 "Olympics")
                                    :poss (c / country
                                          :name (n3 / name
                                                :op1 "Britain"))
                                    :ARG0-of (h / humiliate-01)
                                    :ARG0-of (d2 / disgrace-01))
                              :ARG1-of b
                              :time (d3 / date-entity
                                    :weekday (m / monday)))))
            :ARG1-of (e / earnest-01)))

# ::id 9 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

      :ARG1 (d / dollar)
      :ARG2 (a / against
            :op1 (a2 / and
                  :op1 (e / euro)
                  :op2 (y / yen)
                  :mod (b / both)))
      :time (d2 / date-entity
            :weekday (t / tuesday))
      :concession (d3 / data
            :topic (p / productive-03)
            :ARG1-of (w / weak-02)))

# ::id 10 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

            :ARG0 (p / person
                  :name (n / name
                        :op1 "Al"
                        :op2 "Gore"))
            :ARG1 (s / state
                  :name (n2 / name
                        :op1 "Tennessee")
                  :mod (h / home)
                  :poss p))
      :op2 (l2 / lose-02
            :ARG0 p
            :ARG1 (d / district
                  :mod (g / government-organization
                        :name (n3 / name
                              :op1 "Congress"))
                  :ARG1-of (r / represent-01
                        :ARG0 p
                        :duration (t / temporal-quantity
                              :quant 8
                              :unit (y / year))))
            :mod (a2 / also)))

# ::id 20 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

            :ARG0 p

                  :ARG0-of (u / uphold-01
                        :ARG1 (c3 / control-01
                              :ARG0 (h / hutu)
                              :ARG1 (a / and

                  :quant (m / more))

                        :ARG1 p)
                  :source (a2 / around
                        :op1 (w / world))))
      :ARG1 (s / send-01
            :ARG0 a
            :ARG1 (m2 / message-01
                  :ARG0 a
                  :ARG1 (c2 / congratulate-01
                        :ARG0 a
                        :ARG1 (c3 / congress
                              :mod (n / nation)
                              :poss (p3 / political-party
                                    :name (n2 / name
                                          :op1 "Communist"
                                          :op2 "Party")
                                    :location (c4 / country
                                          :name (n3 / name
                                                :op1 "China")))
                              :ord (o / ordinal-entity
                                    :value 5)))
                  :ARG2 c3)))

(r / report-01
      :ARG0 (a / agency
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "IRNA")
            :mod (n2 / news)
            :mod (o / official))
      :ARG1 (w / write-01
            :ARG0 (c / country
                  :name (n3 / name
                        :op1 "Iran"))
            :ARG1 (l / letter)
            :ARG2 (p / person
                  :name (n4 / name
                        :op1 "Ban"
                        :op2 "Ki-moon")
                  :ARG0-of (c2 / complain-01
                        :ARG1 (a2 / and
                              :op1 (a3 / attack-01
                                    :ARG0 (c3 / country
                                          :name (n5 / name
                                                :op1 "United"
                                                :op2 "States"))
                                    :ARG1 (c4 / consulate
                                          :poss c
                                          :location (c5 / city
                                                :name (n6 / name
                                                      :op1 "Arbil")
                                                :location (n7 / north
                                                      :part-of (c6 / country
                                                            :name (n8 / name
                                                                  :op1 "Iraq")))))
                                    :manner (l2 / law
                                          :polarity -))
                              :op2 (d / detain-01
                                    :ARG0 c3
                                    :ARG1 (p2 / person
                                          :quant 5
                                          :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                                                :ARG1 c
                                                :ARG2 (m / member
                                                      :mod (s / staff))))))))
            :time (d2 / date-entity
                  :weekday (s2 / saturday))))
